# description
time series db. See also 'flux' language

# install
brew install influxdb  # cask
https://dl.influxdata.com/influxdb/releases/influxdb2-2.3.0-darwin-amd64.tar.gz

# docs
https://docs.influxdata.com/influxdb/v2.3/

# usage
influxd
influx config create -n default -u http://localhost:8086 -o example-org -t mySuP3rS3cr3tT0keN -a

# see telegraf
Use Telegraf to quickly write data to InfluxDB Cloud
https://www.influxdata.com/time-series-platform/telegraf/

Collect and write data
Collect and write data to InfluxDB using the Telegraf plugins, the InfluxDB v2 API, the influx command line interface (CLI), the InfluxDB UI (the user interface for InfluxDB 2.3), or the InfluxDB v2 API client libraries.
For details, see Automatically configure Telegraf and Manually update Telegraf configurations.

# Scrape data
InfluxDB OSS lets you scrape Prometheus-formatted metrics from HTTP endpoints. For details, see Scrape data.

# API, CLI, and client libraries
https://docs.influxdata.com/influxdb/v2.3/api/#tag/Write

# Query data
Query data using Flux, the UI, and the influx command line interface. See Query data.

# Process data
Use InfluxDB tasks to process and downsample data. See Process data.

# Visualize data
Build custom dashboards to visualize your data. See Visualize data.

# Monitor and alert
Monitor your data and sends alerts based on specified logic. See Monitor and alert.
